Well names of plate type

Source: R/plates.R
PlateTypeToWellNames.Rd

Lists the well names of a known well plate format, from left to right and top to bottom.

Usage

PlateTypeToWellNames(type = c("6", "96", "384"))

Arguments

type

The name a plate type (character)

Value

Returns a character vector of well names.

See also

Other Plate functions: Plate-class, as.character,Well-method, nextWell(), plateMap(), plateWellVolume(), randomise(), seekReagent(), setWell(), set_block(), sourceReagent()

Other Well functions: Well-class, as.character,Well-method, nextWell(), validRow()

Examples

PlateTypeToWellNames("6")
#> [1] "A01" "A02" "A03" "B01" "B02" "B03"
